\begin_layout Standard
For a discrete probability distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 on the countable set 
\begin_inset Formula $\{x_{1},x_{2},\dots\}$
\end_inset

, with 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}=p(x_{i})$
\end_inset

, the 
\series bold
entropy 
\series default
of 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h(p)=-\sum_{i\ge1}p_{i}\log p_{i}.
\]

\end_inset

For a continuous probability density function 
\begin_inset Formula $p(x)$
\end_inset

 on the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

, its 
\series bold
entropy 
\series default
is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h(p)=-\int_{0}^{1}p(x)\log p(x)dx.
\]

\end_inset


